WEBVTT

NOTE Netflix
NOTE Profile: webvtt-lssdh-ios8
NOTE Date: 2017/02/14 03:26:45

NOTE SegmentIndex
NOTE Segment=598.014 14628@374 105
NOTE Segment=592.717 21259@15002 154
NOTE Segment=593.760 19128@36261 140
NOTE Segment=575.199 16158@55389 119
NOTE Segment=130.172 3749@71547 27
NOTE /SegmentIndex

                                            

                    
1
00:00:02.127 --> 00:00:03.044  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
TARQUIN: <i>Hoshi.</i>

2
00:00:03.128 --> 00:00:05.422  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
ARCHER: <i>Previously on </i>
Star Trek Enterprise...

3
00:00:05.505 --> 00:00:07.090  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
TARQUIN:
I know you're on an urgent mission.

4
00:00:07.173 --> 00:00:08.299  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who are you?

5
00:00:08.383 --> 00:00:09.467  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
TARQUIN: Don't be frightened.

6
00:00:09.551 --> 00:00:11.052  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you want?

7
00:00:11.136 --> 00:00:13.805  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
TARQUIN: You're searching for something.
I can help.

8
00:00:16.224 --> 00:00:18.852  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
HOSHI: <i>He was horrified that </i>
<i>seven million of us were killed.</i>

9
00:00:19.561 --> 00:00:22.939  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>He says he's willing to use his abilities</i>
<i>to help us find the Xindi.</i>

10
00:00:24.149 --> 00:00:25.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's this?

11
00:00:25.692 --> 00:00:28.278  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It helps me extend
the range of my telepathy.

12
00:00:28.361 --> 00:00:30.113  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He gave me these coordinates.

13
00:00:30.196 --> 00:00:32.198  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What are they for?
-A Xindi colony.

14
00:00:32.282 --> 00:00:34.367  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He said they're building
part of the weapon there.

15
00:00:37.829 --> 00:00:39.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're preparing to test the weapon

16
00:00:39.581 --> 00:00:42.917  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
on an uninhabited planet
in the Calindra system.

17
00:00:43.001 --> 00:00:46.004  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But we're going to need
another shipment of Kemocite,

18
00:00:46.963 --> 00:00:49.674  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
at least 100 kilograms.

19
00:00:50.425 --> 00:00:52.719  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll contact Gralik.

20
00:00:52.802 --> 00:00:57.599  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If the test is successful,
how long before we can deploy the weapon?

21
00:00:59.684 --> 00:01:01.061  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A matter of weeks.

22
00:02:32.986 --> 00:02:35.238  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There are no defensive systems.

23
00:02:35.321 --> 00:02:38.491  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
No active sensor sweeps
or artificial satellites.

24
00:02:38.575 --> 00:02:40.994  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
No vessels anywhere in the vicinity.

25
00:02:41.744 --> 00:02:45.081  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
We've seen how different
Xindi technology is.

26
00:02:45.165 --> 00:02:47.458  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
They could have defenses we can't detect.

27
00:02:48.501 --> 00:02:53.339  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
It's also possible that what we were told
about this colony isn't accurate.

28
00:02:54.257 --> 00:02:57.385  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
We're putting a lot of faith
in Hoshi's telepathic friend.

29
00:03:04.142 --> 00:03:06.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
What about these energy readings?

30
00:03:06.436 --> 00:03:08.605  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They could be coming
from a weapons complex.

31
00:03:08.688 --> 00:03:12.692  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They could also be electrical storms,
deposits of diamagnetic ore...

32
00:03:12.775 --> 00:03:14.611  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Or a glitch in our sensors, I know.

33
00:03:14.694 --> 00:03:16.779  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But if there's any chance
that something on that planet

34
00:03:16.863 --> 00:03:19.866  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
could lead us to the Xindi weapon,
we have to investigate it.

35
00:03:23.119 --> 00:03:25.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
After we enter the system,
we'll stay on the far side of that moon.

36
00:03:25.580 --> 00:03:27.206  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It should keep us out of view.

37
00:03:27.582 --> 00:03:30.877  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Tell Major Hayes he'll be
joining us on a reconnaissance mission.

38
00:03:30.960 --> 00:03:32.420  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We launch in two hours.

39
00:03:38.885 --> 00:03:41.346  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-Archer to <i>Enterprise.</i>
-T'POL: <i>Go ahead.</i>

40
00:03:41.429 --> 00:03:42.847  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I've found a landing site

41
00:03:42.931 --> 00:03:45.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
12 kilometers north
of the energy readings.

42
00:03:45.475 --> 00:03:48.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-Any sign they've detected us?
-T'POL: <i>Scans are still negative.</i>

43
00:03:49.312 --> 00:03:50.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>Your signal's breaking up.</i>

44
00:03:51.522 --> 00:03:53.441  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I've set a steep approach vector,

45
00:03:54.484 --> 00:03:55.818  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
and we've ionized the hull.

46
00:03:55.902 --> 00:03:58.279  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
It'll help disperse any scanning beams.

47
00:03:58.363 --> 00:03:59.572  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
T'POL: <i>Acknowledged.</i>

48
00:03:59.656 --> 00:04:02.075  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
If anyone sees us,
they'll think we're a meteor.

49
00:04:14.003 --> 00:04:17.382  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-ARCHER: How much farther?
-MALCOLM: 800 meters.

50
00:04:19.926 --> 00:04:21.427  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Just over that rise.

51
00:04:39.654 --> 00:04:41.698  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's definitely the source
of the energy readings.

52
00:04:51.499 --> 00:04:53.459  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-ARCHER: They're Xindi.
-HAYES: Reptilian?

53
00:04:53.543 --> 00:04:54.460  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

54
00:04:54.544 --> 00:04:57.088  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
One of the other species
we saw in the database.

55
00:05:02.260 --> 00:05:03.970  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
ARCHER: <i>We've picked up readings</i>
<i>across the spectrum...</i>

56
00:05:04.053 --> 00:05:06.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Positron emissions, antiproton bursts.</i>

57
00:05:06.514 --> 00:05:09.017  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Whatever they're doing in there,</i>
<i>it's using a lot of power.</i>

58
00:05:09.100 --> 00:05:11.686  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Corporal Hawkins is standing by
with an assault team.

59
00:05:11.769 --> 00:05:13.730  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Tell him to keep standing by.</i>

60
00:05:13.813 --> 00:05:16.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I'm not ready </i>
<i>to send in the troops just yet.</i>

61
00:05:16.316 --> 00:05:18.568  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>We've checked out</i>
<i>the perimeter of the complex.</i>

62
00:05:18.651 --> 00:05:20.570  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I think we can get inside</i>
<i>without being detected.</i>

63
00:05:20.903 --> 00:05:23.823  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We'll maintain communications silence
inside the complex.

64
00:05:23.906 --> 00:05:26.576  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll contact you at 0400. Archer out.

65
00:05:41.340 --> 00:05:43.593  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not picking up any security devices.

66
00:05:43.676 --> 00:05:44.886  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What about people?

67
00:05:44.969 --> 00:05:49.057  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Approximately 80 inside the complex,
but not within 100 meters.

68
00:06:21.881 --> 00:06:22.882  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Captain.

69
00:06:24.467 --> 00:06:26.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Some kind of radiolytic compound.

70
00:06:26.761 --> 00:06:28.846  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It doesn't match anything in our database.

71
00:06:28.930 --> 00:06:30.807  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's several hundred kilograms
in this room.

72
00:06:30.890 --> 00:06:32.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( clinking )

73
00:06:35.269 --> 00:06:36.646  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( door opens )

74
00:06:36.729 --> 00:06:40.108  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There were impurities
in the last three production cycles.

75
00:06:40.191 --> 00:06:43.361  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We found a ruptured seal
in the tertiary processing chamber.

76
00:06:43.444 --> 00:06:44.612  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's been repaired.

77
00:06:44.695 --> 00:06:47.657  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We'll have to increase the production rate
by at least 60%.

78
00:06:47.740 --> 00:06:49.075  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Assign two additional teams.

79
00:06:49.158 --> 00:06:51.035  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Degra isn't being realistic.

80
00:06:51.119 --> 00:06:54.038  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This facility wasn't designed
to manufacture such large quantities.

81
00:06:57.708 --> 00:07:00.294  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your job is to synthesize Kemocite.

82
00:07:00.378 --> 00:07:02.463  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I suggest you get back to it.

83
00:07:04.507 --> 00:07:06.509  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Have these canisters retested.

84
00:07:06.592 --> 00:07:09.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Salvage what you can,
then destroy the rest.

85
00:07:52.138 --> 00:07:53.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We have it, Captain.

86
00:07:53.514 --> 00:07:55.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
ARCHER: <i>I need an analysis </i>
<i>as soon as possible.</i>

87
00:07:55.850 --> 00:07:57.226  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
T'POL: Acknowledged.

88
00:07:59.353 --> 00:08:04.817  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Captain, this place obviously has
something to do with the weapon.

89
00:08:04.901 --> 00:08:07.153  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It seems to me the sooner
we put it out of commission, the better.

90
00:08:07.236 --> 00:08:08.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Two spatial charges...

91
00:08:08.613 --> 00:08:11.616  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's all it would take
to destroy the complex from orbit.

92
00:08:11.699 --> 00:08:14.410  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That might set them back for a while,

93
00:08:14.494 --> 00:08:17.121  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but we can't lose sight
of our main objective.

94
00:08:17.955 --> 00:08:20.541  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want to know where they're
shipping this Kemocite.

95
00:08:21.542 --> 00:08:23.252  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It could lead us to the weapon.

96
00:09:11.300 --> 00:09:13.010  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have some questions for you.

97
00:09:24.480 --> 00:09:25.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
GRALIK: Who are you?

98
00:09:30.111 --> 00:09:32.071  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you want from me?

99
00:09:32.154 --> 00:09:33.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sit down!

100
00:09:34.615 --> 00:09:36.075  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's nobody else here, sir.

101
00:09:36.158 --> 00:09:37.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Apparently he lives alone.

102
00:09:41.497 --> 00:09:42.957  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Stand watch outside.

103
00:09:50.339 --> 00:09:51.340  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's your name?

104
00:09:52.717 --> 00:09:54.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Gralik Durr.

105
00:09:54.844 --> 00:09:57.430  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My name's Jonathan Archer.

106
00:09:58.014 --> 00:09:59.223  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm from Earth.

107
00:10:00.850 --> 00:10:04.687  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Is that supposed to explain
why you forced your way into my home?

108
00:10:08.899 --> 00:10:10.610  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tell me about Kemocite.

109
00:10:12.445 --> 00:10:14.405  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's a multi-phasic isotope.

110
00:10:14.488 --> 00:10:18.159  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Used for what?
-There are numerous applications.

111
00:10:18.242 --> 00:10:20.453  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It depends on the level of refinement.

112
00:10:25.166 --> 00:10:28.127  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're working with someone named Degra.

113
00:10:30.212 --> 00:10:34.008  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Who is he?
-That's none of your concern.

114
00:10:43.809 --> 00:10:45.353  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's he using it for?

115
00:10:46.062 --> 00:10:49.231  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Kemocite can be used
for any number of purposes.

116
00:10:49.315 --> 00:10:51.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't make a habit
of asking our clients

117
00:10:51.108 --> 00:10:52.735  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
what they plan to do with it.

118
00:10:52.818 --> 00:10:55.279  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe you should,
because this batch is being used

119
00:10:55.363 --> 00:10:57.490  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to create a weapon
to exterminate my people!

120
00:10:58.282 --> 00:10:59.283  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What?

121
00:10:59.367 --> 00:11:00.910  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want to know where
the weapon is being built

122
00:11:00.993 --> 00:11:02.536  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and when it's going to be ready.

123
00:11:02.620 --> 00:11:05.039  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know what you're talking about.

124
00:11:05.122 --> 00:11:07.625  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm not leaving here
until I get the answers I need.

125
00:11:15.591 --> 00:11:19.011  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I managed to identify
a sub-quantum imprint.

126
00:11:19.095 --> 00:11:21.597  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It matches the signature
of the Xindi probe.

127
00:11:21.680 --> 00:11:23.349  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
TUCKER:
There's no doubt about it, Captain.

128
00:11:23.432 --> 00:11:26.352  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This isotope was used in
the weapon that attacked Earth.

129
00:11:26.435 --> 00:11:28.729  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
T'POL: <i>Have you learned anything</i>
<i>from the interrogation?</i>

130
00:11:28.813 --> 00:11:30.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not yet, but this should help.

131
00:11:30.940 --> 00:11:32.525  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
TUCKER: <i>Something else, Captain.</i>

132
00:11:32.608 --> 00:11:34.318  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I ran a scan on that rifle we picked up.

133
00:11:34.402 --> 00:11:37.029  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There it was again,
the same quantum imprint.

134
00:11:37.113 --> 00:11:38.906  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd like permission to take it apart.

135
00:11:40.658 --> 00:11:41.700  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go ahead.

136
00:11:42.410 --> 00:11:44.412  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll contact you in a couple of hours.

137
00:11:44.495 --> 00:11:45.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
T'POL: <i>Understood.</i>

138
00:11:47.915 --> 00:11:49.500  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Congratulations, sir.

139
00:11:50.835 --> 00:11:54.672  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Three months ago, we entered the expanse
with no idea who these Xindi were,

140
00:11:54.755 --> 00:11:56.340  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
or how to find them.

141
00:11:56.424 --> 00:11:59.385  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And now we're about to destroy
one of their weapons facilities.

142
00:12:08.102 --> 00:12:12.106  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
ARCHER: I thought we were here
to try and stop a war, not start one.

143
00:12:12.189 --> 00:12:13.816  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
MALCOLM: They struck first.

144
00:12:13.899 --> 00:12:16.735  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Because they were told
we're going to attack them.

145
00:12:16.819 --> 00:12:19.238  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They think they're acting in self-defense.

146
00:12:19.321 --> 00:12:20.990  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
By destroying this complex,

147
00:12:21.073 --> 00:12:23.951  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we'll be confirming their worst fears
about humanity.

148
00:12:24.034 --> 00:12:27.413  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Let's not forget the seven million people
that were killed.

149
00:12:40.301 --> 00:12:43.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Have Major Hayes lay down
blast suppressors.

150
00:12:45.222 --> 00:12:47.641  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
When this facility goes,

151
00:12:47.725 --> 00:12:50.352  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't want to take the rest
of the settlement with it.

152
00:12:56.275 --> 00:12:58.319  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What about Gralik, sir?

153
00:12:58.402 --> 00:13:00.362  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He'll tell them about <i>Enterprise.</i>

154
00:13:03.407 --> 00:13:06.035  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll deal with Gralik when the time comes.

155
00:13:08.329 --> 00:13:10.998  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't intend to let anyone know
we were here.

156
00:13:14.043 --> 00:13:16.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can't imagine what
the captain wants this for.

157
00:13:16.420 --> 00:13:18.005  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He was quite insistent.

158
00:13:18.088 --> 00:13:21.675  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We ran the quantum analysis three times.

159
00:13:21.759 --> 00:13:23.636  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Doesn't he trust us?

160
00:13:23.719 --> 00:13:26.388  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He said he needed it
to help prove a point.

161
00:13:33.229 --> 00:13:35.356  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How long are you going to keep me here?

162
00:13:35.439 --> 00:13:36.941  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's up to Captain Archer.

163
00:13:37.483 --> 00:13:40.861  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, you can tell him
that I'll be in my study.

164
00:13:40.945 --> 00:13:42.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm afraid you're going
to have to stay right here.

165
00:13:43.072 --> 00:13:45.741  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I have work to do.
-And I'm under orders.

166
00:13:46.033 --> 00:13:47.243  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Please sit down.

167
00:13:49.286 --> 00:13:51.455  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've already told you everything I know.

168
00:13:52.790 --> 00:13:54.625  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( door opens )

169
00:13:54.708 --> 00:13:56.293  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah, Captain Archer.

170
00:13:56.377 --> 00:13:58.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was beginning to think
you'd forgotten about me.

171
00:14:06.136 --> 00:14:08.472  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You said you weren't involved
in building weapons.

172
00:14:08.931 --> 00:14:10.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's correct.

173
00:14:10.975 --> 00:14:12.309  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Explain this.

174
00:14:19.817 --> 00:14:21.277  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know what this is.

175
00:14:21.360 --> 00:14:24.321  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's a fragment of a probe
that murdered seven million people.

176
00:14:25.072 --> 00:14:26.156  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( clatters )

177
00:14:29.076 --> 00:14:31.745  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The dead pilot was Xindi.

178
00:14:31.829 --> 00:14:33.664  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The alloy is Xindi.

179
00:14:33.747 --> 00:14:35.583  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And it's imprinted
with the quantum signature

180
00:14:35.666 --> 00:14:37.668  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
of the compound you produce here!

181
00:14:37.751 --> 00:14:40.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We know you're constructing
a larger version of the weapon

182
00:14:40.963 --> 00:14:42.506  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
big enough to destroy a planet.

183
00:14:42.590 --> 00:14:44.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I want to know where it's being built!

184
00:14:46.510 --> 00:14:48.888  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You burst into my home,

185
00:14:49.346 --> 00:14:54.143  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
show me some twisted piece of metal,

186
00:14:54.226 --> 00:14:58.314  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and tell me it proves I'm a mass murderer?

187
00:14:59.440 --> 00:15:01.734  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've never seen your species before.

188
00:15:01.817 --> 00:15:03.861  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've never heard of a planet called Earth,

189
00:15:03.944 --> 00:15:05.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and whether you believe me or not,

190
00:15:05.654 --> 00:15:08.824  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I had nothing to do
with killing millions of its inhabitants.

191
00:15:16.540 --> 00:15:19.209  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm flattered you requested
my assistance, Commander,

192
00:15:19.293 --> 00:15:22.671  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but, uh, weaponry isn't exactly
my area of expertise.

193
00:15:22.755 --> 00:15:25.633  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, my scans of this thing
showed organic components.

194
00:15:25.716 --> 00:15:28.969  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And I figured anything biological
is more your turf than mine.

195
00:15:36.018 --> 00:15:37.561  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you think?

196
00:15:39.772 --> 00:15:42.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They appear to be generating
synaptic impulses.

197
00:15:50.157 --> 00:15:51.492  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is it alive?

198
00:15:55.079 --> 00:15:59.083  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Wouldn't make a very good pet, but...
( sniffs ) Definitely organic.

199
00:15:59.959 --> 00:16:00.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( squishing )

200
00:16:05.047 --> 00:16:07.967  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And it seems to have
reproductive capabilities.

201
00:16:12.179 --> 00:16:15.099  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Kemocite is extremely refined.

202
00:16:15.182 --> 00:16:18.435  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Did it come from this facility?
-It did.

203
00:16:19.311 --> 00:16:23.190  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We supply many species with Kemocite,
not just Xindi.

204
00:16:23.273 --> 00:16:25.776  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It has countless applications.

205
00:16:26.360 --> 00:16:29.321  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When Degra requested shipments
so highly refined,

206
00:16:29.405 --> 00:16:30.948  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
we celebrated,

207
00:16:31.031 --> 00:16:34.284  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
realizing the wealth it would bring
to our colony.

208
00:16:34.368 --> 00:16:37.788  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We never considered why he
wanted such pure Kemocite.

209
00:16:37.871 --> 00:16:41.208  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Perhaps our greed blinded us
from the possibility

210
00:16:41.291 --> 00:16:43.961  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that it would be used
in constructing a weapon.

211
00:16:44.044 --> 00:16:48.924  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Is Degra a reptilian?
-No. He's a Xindi-primate.

212
00:16:50.426 --> 00:16:53.470  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I met one at a mining complex.

213
00:16:53.554 --> 00:16:56.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're similar to you, apelike.

214
00:16:56.515 --> 00:17:00.728  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Degra and his people have
always been fair, truthful.

215
00:17:00.811 --> 00:17:02.604  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That may have been why I believed him

216
00:17:02.688 --> 00:17:04.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
when he said the shipment
was for research.

217
00:17:05.065 --> 00:17:10.946  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Perhaps they've become
as untrustworthy as the reptilians.

218
00:17:11.030 --> 00:17:13.449  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've run into a few of them too.

219
00:17:14.783 --> 00:17:20.164  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's hard to imagine five sentient species
evolving on the same planet.

220
00:17:20.247 --> 00:17:21.790  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Five?

221
00:17:22.791 --> 00:17:24.793  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm... I suppose there are now.

222
00:17:28.547 --> 00:17:30.049  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-No, thanks.
-Do you mind?

223
00:17:30.549 --> 00:17:31.592  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, go ahead.

224
00:17:36.847 --> 00:17:38.098  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mmm.

225
00:17:39.058 --> 00:17:43.145  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There was a sixth species, the avians.

226
00:17:43.228 --> 00:17:44.980  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They've been gone since the war.

227
00:17:45.064 --> 00:17:47.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Gone?
-Extinct.

228
00:17:47.357 --> 00:17:53.447  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As far as I'm told, none of them fled
before our homeworld was destroyed.

229
00:17:53.530 --> 00:17:56.784  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We found some debris. How did it happen?

230
00:17:57.367 --> 00:17:59.661  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The war went on for nearly 100 years.

231
00:18:00.245 --> 00:18:01.747  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The sides changed.

232
00:18:01.830 --> 00:18:04.249  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Alliances were forged and then broken.

233
00:18:04.333 --> 00:18:05.417  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
By the time it ended,

234
00:18:05.501 --> 00:18:09.129  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I doubt any of the six species
remembered what started it.

235
00:18:09.546 --> 00:18:11.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But everyone remembered what ended it.

236
00:18:13.092 --> 00:18:16.261  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As well as being unstable politically,

237
00:18:16.345 --> 00:18:20.724  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
our planet was even more
unstable geologically.

238
00:18:22.893 --> 00:18:26.271  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In a final desperate act,

239
00:18:26.355 --> 00:18:30.609  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the insectoids and reptilians
detonated massive explosions

240
00:18:30.692 --> 00:18:33.779  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
beneath the eight largest
seismic fissures.

241
00:18:36.615 --> 00:18:41.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'd like to think they didn't realize
how devastating the result would be.

242
00:18:47.835 --> 00:18:50.170  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My grandfather lived there.

243
00:18:50.254 --> 00:18:51.755  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He told me of places

244
00:18:51.839 --> 00:18:56.051  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
where the sky was sometimes
filled with avians.

245
00:18:58.512 --> 00:19:00.055  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now they're gone.

246
00:19:04.309 --> 00:19:07.604  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The other five species did survive.

247
00:19:07.688 --> 00:19:11.942  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
From what I can tell, they don't all live
on remote colonies like this one.

248
00:19:12.025 --> 00:19:17.114  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The descendants of those that escaped
are scattered across the expanse.

249
00:19:18.907 --> 00:19:23.328  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Many live peaceful lives,
but obviously not all.

250
00:19:23.412 --> 00:19:25.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( door opens )
-HAYES: Captain.

251
00:19:25.956 --> 00:19:27.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll be right back.

252
00:19:27.541 --> 00:19:28.709  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sir.

253
00:19:32.504 --> 00:19:33.881  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's OK.

254
00:19:36.466 --> 00:19:38.093  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The suppressors are in place.

255
00:19:38.177 --> 00:19:41.096  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The blast wave should be mostly
confined to the facility.

256
00:19:41.180 --> 00:19:43.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Sir, I noticed a lot of activity
down there.

257
00:19:43.515 --> 00:19:45.475  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It seemed like something is going on.

258
00:19:45.559 --> 00:19:47.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( communicator beeps )

259
00:19:49.271 --> 00:19:50.647  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Archer.

260
00:19:50.731 --> 00:19:53.609  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
T'POL: <i>Captain, we've detected a ship</i>
<i>approaching the planet.</i>

261
00:19:53.901 --> 00:19:57.613  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>The hull configuration matches </i>
<i>the Xindi vessel that attacked us. </i>

262
00:20:00.365 --> 00:20:01.450  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Reptilians.

263
00:20:24.431 --> 00:20:26.058  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Recognize anyone?

264
00:20:27.309 --> 00:20:29.144  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( inaudible )

265
00:20:32.314 --> 00:20:35.734  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The reptilians seem
rather upset about something.

266
00:20:52.793 --> 00:20:54.336  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You got something?

267
00:20:54.419 --> 00:20:57.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've been running scans
of the weapon's organic component.

268
00:20:57.756 --> 00:21:02.010  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Its neural pathways appear to help
modulate the rifle's power output.

269
00:21:02.094 --> 00:21:03.553  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's the most sophisticated example

270
00:21:03.637 --> 00:21:05.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
of biomechanical engineering
I've ever seen.

271
00:21:05.597 --> 00:21:07.891  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You said you had good news, Doc.
-Ah, yes.

272
00:21:08.392 --> 00:21:11.478  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've been attempting to break down
this creature's immune system.

273
00:21:12.229 --> 00:21:14.064  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're trying to make it sick?

274
00:21:14.147 --> 00:21:16.650  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Mmm-hmm. However, it's proving
to be quite resilient.

275
00:21:16.733 --> 00:21:19.319  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've tried an array
of viruses and pathogens,

276
00:21:19.403 --> 00:21:20.779  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but it's immune to all of them.

277
00:21:20.862 --> 00:21:24.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then I began exposing it
to various radioactive spectra.

278
00:21:26.285 --> 00:21:28.912  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A sustained burst of delta radiation.

279
00:21:33.125 --> 00:21:36.378  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If we rig up portable E.M. emitters,

280
00:21:36.461 --> 00:21:37.838  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
we could knock out reptilian weapons

281
00:21:37.921 --> 00:21:39.881  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
before any of them get a chance
to pull the trigger.

282
00:21:39.965 --> 00:21:41.216  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In theory.

283
00:21:41.300 --> 00:21:43.510  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Unfortunately, the amount
of radiation required

284
00:21:43.593 --> 00:21:46.596  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
would be extremely hazardous
to any humans in the area.

285
00:21:46.680 --> 00:21:48.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-It's still a place to start.
-Hmm...

286
00:21:48.515 --> 00:21:50.392  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Great work, Doc. Keep at it.

287
00:21:50.475 --> 00:21:52.853  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, and, uh, Commander...

288
00:21:52.936 --> 00:21:56.398  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'd avoid exposing
any of the Xindi technology

289
00:21:56.481 --> 00:21:58.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to omicron radiation.

290
00:21:59.067 --> 00:22:02.154  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It seems to thrive on it, as you can see.

291
00:22:02.654 --> 00:22:05.073  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I'll keep that in mind.
-Hmm...

292
00:22:06.116 --> 00:22:07.617  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're ahead of schedule.

293
00:22:07.701 --> 00:22:10.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We weren't expecting them
for another three days.

294
00:22:10.579 --> 00:22:13.790  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You might not have much time left
to accomplish your mission.

295
00:22:13.874 --> 00:22:15.542  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What makes you say that?

296
00:22:15.625 --> 00:22:19.588  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've been processing Kemocite for them
for nearly six months.

297
00:22:19.671 --> 00:22:23.133  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're here for their final shipment.

298
00:22:23.216 --> 00:22:27.220  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Captain, I'm the primary technician
at this facility.

299
00:22:27.304 --> 00:22:30.140  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They'll want to talk to me
before accepting delivery,

300
00:22:30.223 --> 00:22:33.769  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to confirm that all of their
technical requirements have been met.

301
00:22:35.187 --> 00:22:40.484  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I may be able to obtain
some information for you

302
00:22:40.567 --> 00:22:42.486  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
about this weapon.

303
00:22:44.071 --> 00:22:47.199  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That could be dangerous.

304
00:22:47.282 --> 00:22:49.076  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm willing to take that risk.

305
00:22:54.289 --> 00:22:58.251  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How do I know you won't expose us,
tell them about <i>Enterprise?</i>

306
00:22:58.335 --> 00:23:02.130  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm proud of my craft, Captain.

307
00:23:02.214 --> 00:23:05.258  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've practiced it for many years.

308
00:23:05.342 --> 00:23:09.721  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I won't let my work be corrupted
in this way.

309
00:23:09.805 --> 00:23:13.767  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Seven million people.

310
00:23:15.185 --> 00:23:19.064  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If I'd chosen my clients more carefully,

311
00:23:19.147 --> 00:23:21.942  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that tragedy might not have happened.

312
00:23:23.026 --> 00:23:26.321  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't intend to let it happen again.

313
00:23:27.739 --> 00:23:29.116  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( communicator beeps )

314
00:23:32.452 --> 00:23:33.578  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Archer.

315
00:23:33.662 --> 00:23:36.456  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
MALCOLM: <i>Captain, there are two </i>
<i>Xindi bio-signs heading this way.</i>

316
00:23:53.640 --> 00:23:55.934  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
XINDI MALE: Gralik, are you there?

317
00:23:58.436 --> 00:23:59.646  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Gralik?

318
00:24:00.981 --> 00:24:02.357  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( door chimes )

319
00:24:22.794 --> 00:24:24.921  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Degra's probably wondering where I am.

320
00:24:25.005 --> 00:24:27.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
His companions don't like
to be kept waiting.

321
00:24:27.883 --> 00:24:28.884  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( knock on door )

322
00:24:31.344 --> 00:24:32.804  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
MALCOLM: Captain.

323
00:24:35.599 --> 00:24:36.808  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They've gone.

324
00:24:36.892 --> 00:24:39.936  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They'll return,
probably with armed reptilians.

325
00:24:40.020 --> 00:24:42.272  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just because you didn't show up for work?

326
00:24:42.355 --> 00:24:45.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There are fewer than 100 people
on this planet.

327
00:24:45.108 --> 00:24:48.069  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It doesn't go unnoticed
when one of them is missing.

328
00:24:49.070 --> 00:24:51.072  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Degra won't leave until he sees

329
00:24:51.156 --> 00:24:54.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the results
of the final isotopic analysis.

330
00:24:54.492 --> 00:24:56.745  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You should reconsider my offer.

331
00:25:00.290 --> 00:25:01.875  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
TUCKER: That's good, right there.

332
00:25:02.584 --> 00:25:04.002  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you sure this is wise?

333
00:25:04.085 --> 00:25:05.921  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's four inches of solid duranium.

334
00:25:06.004 --> 00:25:07.797  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If this thing can blast a hole through it,

335
00:25:07.881 --> 00:25:09.716  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
then we're in even worse trouble
than we thought.

336
00:25:09.799 --> 00:25:13.803  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Still, it might be prudent to find
a more suitable environment to test it.

337
00:25:13.887 --> 00:25:16.264  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We don't have time to go looking
for some deserted asteroid,

338
00:25:16.348 --> 00:25:17.515  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
if that's what you mean.

339
00:25:17.599 --> 00:25:20.018  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If I may, Commander Tucker and I
have learned all we can

340
00:25:20.101 --> 00:25:21.811  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
from examining the workings of the device.

341
00:25:21.895 --> 00:25:24.731  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A practical test is the next logical step.

342
00:25:25.523 --> 00:25:28.276  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've rigged up four of Malcolm's
force-field emitters.

343
00:25:30.695 --> 00:25:32.614  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They'll contain any blast debris.

344
00:25:32.697 --> 00:25:35.659  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What about radiation
or particle disbursement?

345
00:25:35.742 --> 00:25:38.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You know nothing about this device.
-That's the point.

346
00:25:38.578 --> 00:25:40.538  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Those Xindi took out
half of our security force

347
00:25:40.622 --> 00:25:41.957  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
when they came aboard.

348
00:25:42.040 --> 00:25:43.375  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now, if we don't start
making some progress

349
00:25:43.458 --> 00:25:44.793  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
understanding their weapons,

350
00:25:44.876 --> 00:25:48.171  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we won't stand a chance in hell
of beating them when the time comes.

351
00:25:53.343 --> 00:25:55.345  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let me know when you're ready.

352
00:25:55.428 --> 00:25:56.930  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Give us an hour.

353
00:26:09.609 --> 00:26:11.319  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
More delays?

354
00:26:11.403 --> 00:26:13.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We did surprise them by arriving early.

355
00:26:13.655 --> 00:26:15.282  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's no excuse.

356
00:26:15.365 --> 00:26:18.326  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They should have been ready by now.

357
00:26:18.410 --> 00:26:20.370  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Such lethargic creatures.

358
00:26:21.538 --> 00:26:23.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You could learn something from them...

359
00:26:24.082 --> 00:26:25.709  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Patience, for example.

360
00:26:25.792 --> 00:26:27.210  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( hisses )

361
00:26:28.044 --> 00:26:29.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where's Gralik?

362
00:26:29.713 --> 00:26:31.256  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We can't find him.

363
00:26:31.548 --> 00:26:34.551  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In a complex this size,
how difficult could it be?

364
00:26:34.634 --> 00:26:37.304  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've searched everywhere.
No one's seen him.

365
00:26:37.387 --> 00:26:39.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He often takes walks
outside the settlement.

366
00:26:39.597 --> 00:26:40.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Walks?

367
00:26:41.141 --> 00:26:43.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Without his analysis, I can't proceed.

368
00:26:43.435 --> 00:26:45.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've organized search teams.

369
00:26:45.186 --> 00:26:49.107  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We don't have time for you to go
foraging through the forest.

370
00:26:49.190 --> 00:26:51.234  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll find him ourselves.

371
00:27:06.750 --> 00:27:08.418  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( scanner beeping )

372
00:27:08.501 --> 00:27:09.836  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is it?

373
00:27:09.919 --> 00:27:12.172  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Someone's closing on our position, sir.

374
00:27:12.255 --> 00:27:13.340  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
400 meters.

375
00:27:13.423 --> 00:27:16.301  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Reptilians?
-I'm not certain.

376
00:27:16.384 --> 00:27:18.970  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-350 meters.
-Stay with him.

377
00:27:24.351 --> 00:27:25.977  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Still closing, sir.

378
00:27:26.895 --> 00:27:29.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
200 meters. 150.

379
00:27:29.773 --> 00:27:31.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're bloody fast, whoever they are.

380
00:27:36.154 --> 00:27:37.155  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Take cover!

381
00:28:13.483 --> 00:28:15.318  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( electricity buzzing )

382
00:28:17.112 --> 00:28:21.199  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's a seeker. The reptilians
built them for reconnaissance.

383
00:28:21.282 --> 00:28:24.786  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They were used to great effect
during the war.

384
00:28:24.869 --> 00:28:27.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It seems as though you may have
been exposed after all.

385
00:28:30.792 --> 00:28:32.502  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Let's hope they didn't get
a very good look at us.

386
00:28:32.585 --> 00:28:34.838  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There are some caves not far ahead.

387
00:28:34.921 --> 00:28:39.718  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They should provide us with cover
in case we encounter any more of those.

388
00:28:54.482 --> 00:28:57.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Ready, Doc?
-Ready.

389
00:29:01.573 --> 00:29:03.074  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( weapon clicks )

390
00:29:07.912 --> 00:29:10.373  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What's wrong?
-It won't fire.

391
00:29:10.457 --> 00:29:11.750  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't understand.

392
00:29:11.833 --> 00:29:13.460  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Perhaps it has a safety device.

393
00:29:13.543 --> 00:29:14.627  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( beeping )

394
00:29:14.711 --> 00:29:17.297  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What's that?
-It's coming from the weapon.

395
00:29:19.883 --> 00:29:21.426  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Looks like some kind of countdown.

396
00:29:23.344 --> 00:29:25.513  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The energy levels are increasing.

397
00:29:26.723 --> 00:29:27.891  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's overloading.

398
00:29:28.767 --> 00:29:30.977  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can't shut it down.
Damn thing's booby-trapped.

399
00:29:31.060 --> 00:29:33.646  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-If you remove the power cell...
-It'll just grow back.

400
00:29:44.491 --> 00:29:46.326  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans )

401
00:30:01.966 --> 00:30:03.218  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

402
00:30:06.304 --> 00:30:07.847  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Quick thinking, Commander.

403
00:30:07.931 --> 00:30:09.390  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You were right.

404
00:30:09.474 --> 00:30:13.478  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We probably should have found a nice,
empty asteroid to test it on.

405
00:30:20.735 --> 00:30:24.239  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Xindi ship is still in orbit.
We haven't detected any other vessels.

406
00:30:24.322 --> 00:30:25.865  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Understood.

407
00:30:25.949 --> 00:30:28.743  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Captain, if the Xindi </i>
<i>have detected your presence,</i>

408
00:30:28.827 --> 00:30:31.162  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I strongly urge you to return to the ship.

409
00:30:31.246 --> 00:30:32.705  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
ARCHER: <i>I appreciate your concern.</i>

410
00:30:32.789 --> 00:30:36.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But we still have a few loose ends
to tie up down here.

411
00:30:36.084 --> 00:30:37.460  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Archer out.

412
00:30:39.546 --> 00:30:42.590  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Anything?
-No, sir.

413
00:30:42.674 --> 00:30:44.342  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We just might have stopped
those bloodhounds

414
00:30:44.425 --> 00:30:46.511  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
before they transmitted our position.

415
00:30:48.137 --> 00:30:49.430  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's hope so.

416
00:30:54.936 --> 00:30:56.855  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No sign of the reptilians.

417
00:30:56.938 --> 00:30:59.399  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I doubt they'll find us.

418
00:30:59.482 --> 00:31:02.110  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's topaline ore.

419
00:31:02.193 --> 00:31:04.445  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It should disrupt their scanners.

420
00:31:04.529 --> 00:31:07.365  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Even their seekers won't locate us here.

421
00:31:12.036 --> 00:31:14.706  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you intend to do now, Captain?

422
00:31:16.207 --> 00:31:18.626  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Destroy our facility?

423
00:31:18.710 --> 00:31:21.546  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you plan to wait until I'm back inside,

424
00:31:21.629 --> 00:31:25.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or will you simply dispose of me
here in the forest?

425
00:31:27.594 --> 00:31:32.724  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I've been considering another option.
-I'd certainly like to hear it.

426
00:31:34.809 --> 00:31:36.728  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The people on this colony
had nothing to do

427
00:31:36.811 --> 00:31:38.938  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
with the attack on my planet.

428
00:31:41.065 --> 00:31:43.192  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll be damned if I'm gonna
make them pay for it.

429
00:31:46.029 --> 00:31:49.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You offered to help us.
Are you still willing?

430
00:31:52.035 --> 00:31:54.287  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If you're prepared to trust me.

431
00:31:59.876 --> 00:32:04.130  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then we'll give them their Kemocite,

432
00:32:04.213 --> 00:32:07.216  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but it won't be exactly what they ordered.

433
00:32:14.140 --> 00:32:16.809  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Make sure he gets home safely.
-Yes, sir.

434
00:32:20.855 --> 00:32:23.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It would be better if I went alone.

435
00:32:33.910 --> 00:32:34.911  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good luck.

436
00:32:38.206 --> 00:32:39.374  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And you.

437
00:32:44.295 --> 00:32:47.173  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-MALCOLM: Permission to speak freely.
-Go ahead.

438
00:32:48.967 --> 00:32:51.886  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not sure it was wise to let him go.

439
00:32:51.970 --> 00:32:53.972  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He could lead the reptilians back here.

440
00:32:54.055 --> 00:32:56.057  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you speaking freely as well, Major?

441
00:32:56.140 --> 00:32:59.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Just offering a tactical assessment, sir.
-Noted.

442
00:33:01.896 --> 00:33:03.439  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He said he'd help us.

443
00:33:05.066 --> 00:33:06.317  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I believe him.

444
00:33:07.276 --> 00:33:08.277  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( computer beeps )

445
00:33:08.361 --> 00:33:10.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's the captain.

446
00:33:10.655 --> 00:33:12.073  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go ahead, sir.

447
00:33:12.156 --> 00:33:14.617  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
ARCHER: <i>Tell the armory </i>
<i>to hold off on those spatial charges.</i>

448
00:33:14.701 --> 00:33:16.119  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>There's been a change of plans.</i>

449
00:33:16.202 --> 00:33:20.164  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Is everything all right?
-I'll let you know in a couple of hours.

450
00:33:20.248 --> 00:33:22.834  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Right now,
I have an assignment for you and Hoshi.

451
00:33:37.056 --> 00:33:38.474  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're looking for you.

452
00:33:38.558 --> 00:33:40.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Have you started loading the shipment?

453
00:33:40.643 --> 00:33:42.437  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Not yet.
-Good.

454
00:33:42.520 --> 00:33:45.606  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I want to run another refinement test.

455
00:33:45.690 --> 00:33:47.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've completed three already.

456
00:33:47.483 --> 00:33:49.402  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The impurities were
less than six parts per million.

457
00:33:49.485 --> 00:33:53.406  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have to be absolutely certain
that we've met their specifications.

458
00:33:53.489 --> 00:33:56.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know how important this is
to all of us.

459
00:33:56.951 --> 00:33:58.286  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We should get started.

460
00:33:58.369 --> 00:34:02.749  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You two perform the isotopic analysis.
I'll run the submolecular scans.

461
00:34:16.137 --> 00:34:17.847  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've got it.

462
00:34:17.930 --> 00:34:20.016  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've modified the radiolytic signature.

463
00:34:20.099 --> 00:34:22.643  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you can get it on board their ship,
I'll be able to track it.

464
00:34:22.727 --> 00:34:23.978  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Understood.

465
00:34:40.495 --> 00:34:41.996  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where were you?

466
00:34:42.080 --> 00:34:44.665  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My personal activities
aren't your concern.

467
00:34:44.749 --> 00:34:48.628  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And do your personal activities
involve destroying one of our seekers?

468
00:34:48.711 --> 00:34:50.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was hunting tree scarabs.

469
00:34:51.047 --> 00:34:52.965  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your drone was frightening them.

470
00:34:53.049 --> 00:34:54.634  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who was with you?

471
00:34:54.717 --> 00:34:57.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I prefer to spend my time
in the forest alone.

472
00:34:57.595 --> 00:35:00.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Our scans detected other bio-signs.

473
00:35:00.848 --> 00:35:01.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was alone.

474
00:35:02.058 --> 00:35:04.519  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you saw the drone,
you knew we were here.

475
00:35:04.602 --> 00:35:06.312  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why didn't you return?

476
00:35:06.395 --> 00:35:08.022  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're two days early.

477
00:35:09.357 --> 00:35:11.901  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What are you doing?
-Running some final tests.

478
00:35:11.984 --> 00:35:13.361  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What kind of tests?

479
00:35:13.444 --> 00:35:14.987  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We were told the shipment was ready.

480
00:35:16.781 --> 00:35:20.701  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
42 years. That's how long
I've been running this facility.

481
00:35:20.785 --> 00:35:24.122  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And never once have I allowed
a single gram of Kemocite

482
00:35:24.205 --> 00:35:27.208  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to leave the premises
unless it was perfectly calibrated.

483
00:35:27.291 --> 00:35:28.751  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I take pride in my work,

484
00:35:28.835 --> 00:35:32.839  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but if you're so eager to get underway,
then go ahead, take your shipment!

485
00:35:32.922 --> 00:35:34.340  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But if it doesn't meet your requirements,

486
00:35:34.423 --> 00:35:37.552  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
don't expect me to produce
another 100 kilograms overnight,

487
00:35:37.635 --> 00:35:40.763  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
because we do have
other clients besides you.

488
00:35:43.599 --> 00:35:45.393  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Finish quickly.

489
00:36:10.126 --> 00:36:12.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
MALCOLM: There are two of them,
loading containers.

490
00:36:12.670 --> 00:36:14.088  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Stand by, Captain.

491
00:36:14.172 --> 00:36:15.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Acknowledged.

492
00:36:19.635 --> 00:36:22.054  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-MALCOLM: They're heading back.
-You're clear, sir.

493
00:36:56.881 --> 00:36:58.591  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( beep )
<i>-Reed to </i>Enterprise.

494
00:37:00.218 --> 00:37:01.552  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go ahead.

495
00:37:01.636 --> 00:37:04.347  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
MALCOLM:
<i>The Captain's inside the Xindi shuttle.</i>

496
00:37:04.430 --> 00:37:05.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Acknowledged.

497
00:37:40.299 --> 00:37:43.719  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Captain, three Xindi have
just come out of the complex.

498
00:37:45.346 --> 00:37:46.639  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Understood.

499
00:37:47.765 --> 00:37:49.392  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lieutenant Reed, report.

500
00:37:49.475 --> 00:37:52.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
MALCOLM: <i>We've run into a small problem. </i>
<i>Stand by.</i>

501
00:37:59.568 --> 00:38:01.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We appreciate your efforts.

502
00:38:01.195 --> 00:38:03.447  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Perhaps you'll need our services
in the future.

503
00:38:04.407 --> 00:38:05.408  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Perhaps.

504
00:38:24.135 --> 00:38:26.721  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll miss the pleasure of your company.

505
00:38:26.804 --> 00:38:28.681  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We should go, Degra.

506
00:38:28.764 --> 00:38:30.474  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're behind schedule already.

507
00:38:30.725 --> 00:38:33.769  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've invested a great deal
in this project.

508
00:38:33.853 --> 00:38:35.479  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And you've been well paid for it.

509
00:38:35.771 --> 00:38:37.315  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, you've been more than generous,

510
00:38:37.398 --> 00:38:42.695  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I'd appreciate if you could tell me
what this shipment is being used for.

511
00:38:50.161 --> 00:38:52.079  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't think
it's an unreasonable request.

512
00:38:52.163 --> 00:38:53.372  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It doesn't concern you.

513
00:38:53.456 --> 00:38:55.666  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It concerns all of us.

514
00:38:56.625 --> 00:38:59.086  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've learned
there's a threat to our people.

515
00:39:00.212 --> 00:39:01.589  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What kind of threat?

516
00:39:01.964 --> 00:39:04.383  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A ruthless alien species.

517
00:39:04.467 --> 00:39:06.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If we don't act, they'll destroy us.

518
00:39:17.438 --> 00:39:19.273  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm glad we could contribute.

519
00:39:19.690 --> 00:39:21.525  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Take pride in what you've done here.

520
00:39:35.373 --> 00:39:37.249  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( beep )
<i>-Archer to </i>Enterprise.

521
00:39:38.793 --> 00:39:40.086  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go ahead.

522
00:39:40.169 --> 00:39:42.129  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>What's the status of that Xindi ship?</i>

523
00:39:42.213 --> 00:39:44.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It broke orbit five minutes ago, Captain.

524
00:39:44.632 --> 00:39:46.342  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Are you picking up the tracking signal?</i>

525
00:39:46.425 --> 00:39:47.927  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( beeping )
-Loud and clear.

526
00:39:48.010 --> 00:39:51.263  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Keep an eye on it. </i>
<i>We'll be back as soon as we can.</i>

527
00:39:51.347 --> 00:39:52.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Acknowledged.

528
00:40:01.816 --> 00:40:04.110  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Thank you.
-Mmm...

529
00:40:06.529 --> 00:40:08.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is something wrong?

530
00:40:13.744 --> 00:40:18.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I may have just betrayed my people
to a ruthless alien species.

531
00:40:21.168 --> 00:40:23.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I promise you, you haven't.

532
00:40:24.755 --> 00:40:26.173  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Please trust me.

533
00:40:29.051 --> 00:40:30.094  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
To trust.

534
00:40:37.435 --> 00:40:42.398  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Eventually, Degra's going to discover
that you sabotaged his Kemocite.

535
00:40:42.481 --> 00:40:45.693  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( chuckles ) It should delay
their progress considerably.

536
00:40:45.776 --> 00:40:47.778  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-They'll come back here.
-Don't worry.

537
00:40:47.862 --> 00:40:49.947  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can deal with Degra and his friends.

538
00:40:50.030 --> 00:40:52.825  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You should just be concerned
with finding this weapon.

539
00:40:55.828 --> 00:40:59.832  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Their ship entered an energy portal
after it left orbit.

540
00:41:00.791 --> 00:41:02.793  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've lost our tracking signal.

541
00:41:02.877 --> 00:41:06.714  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The portal's range
is only a few light-years. Keep searching.

542
00:41:12.595 --> 00:41:14.388  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I better get back to <i>Enterprise.</i>

543
00:41:16.515 --> 00:41:22.104  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If everything you've told me is true
about the attack on your world,

544
00:41:23.105 --> 00:41:27.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I hope you remember that
all Xindi are not your enemy.

545
00:41:28.819 --> 00:41:29.862  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will.

